projects.description:
“Design studio for a robotics system controlled by Microsoft Kinect” 

Goals: Design a system that is able to be controlled by gestures with Microsoft Kinect, using the e Skeletal Viewer for the motion tracking.

Achievements: System will be used for further studies in the Mechatronics Laboratory.
 Programming: code written in C++ using FRC libraries for Kinect and implemented on Labview,

 Main Tasks:
 • Study and utilization of NUI libraries;
 • Study and utilization of the graphic interface implemented on a driver station for Labview;
 • using the reference of angles provided by the skeleton function, realize the calculations to acquire the gestures and their sensitivity;
 • control of the delivered power and speed to the actuators;
 • use of multiple planes for gestures acquiring

profile_positions.description:
Job Mission
To design, maintain, and optimize production processes and adapt to changed output requirements. Develop and apply methods of measuring the performance of the production process. Support the Production in order to ensure product quality, short lead-times and ‘short time to market’.

Job Description
Production Engineer on NXE Source CO2, including: Coarse and fine setup of the CO2 laser beam path from Drive Laser to tin droplet, including the workcenters for FFA-OP and BTS.

Generic:
As EF Production Engineer I contribute to the 4 main PE drivers:
• Decrease cycle time;
• Decrease cost;
• Increase efficiency;
• Increase quality.
I have constant attention for safety.  
Although working from a competence group, flexibility is expected, to secure the EF output plans and cycle time roadmaps.

Continuous Improvement:
• Continuously adapt, optimize operating instructions, process flow charts, routings, process parameters and indicators; 
• Analyze the production process (Cycle time and Labor Hours), points out structural problems and bottlenecks, work out suggestions for improvements and initiates their implementation, often in close cooperation with the surrounded departments as Development, Supply Chain and Customer Support.

Support:
• Contribute to the rapid solution of complex faults and take the necessary initiatives and practical decisions;
• Troubleshoot;
• For regular support stand-by might be required.
New Product Introduction:
• I  Use my knowledge in product or process development projects, in order to foresee production problems in the design phase and improve the manufacturability of the product;
• I am actively involved in the release for volume takeover from D&E to Manufacturing.

Introduction:
 The sector operations within the Twinscan Factory is responsible for the production of wafer steppers and scanners as well as for purchasing and logistics. The complete production process of the most advanced machines takes place within this sector. The department Build Operations within Manufacturing is responsible for the assembly and qualification of the various machines and modules of the ASML systems according to strict quality standards.

Job Description:
 - Electrical measuraments and Sensors Analisys in order to parameterize MCs to the design specifications.
 - Analysis and solving of disturbances during the qualification process;
 - Identify structural issues and support diagnostics ;
 - Functional testing of the wafer stage and / or Position Modules
 - Connection of wafer stage to the testrig and placement (including a.o. leak testing) of PM’s;
 - Mechanical adjustments;
 - Disconnection of wafer stage and transfer to upstream customer.
 - Plan and prioritize own work;
 - Report, inform and escalate correctly and timely on progress and status;
 - Actively seek for relevant knowledge;
 - Share and train knowledge and skills.
